        <item>
            <title>Version 1.3.0</title>
            <pubDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2026 15:10:00 +0900</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>7</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.3.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>13.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <h2>Hook-driven status detection</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>SwitchBoard now registers itself as Claude Code Stop/Notification/UserPromptSubmit hooks on launch, replacing the ~3 second polling lag with instant transitions.</li>
                    <li>Hooks are merged safely into <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code> — any existing user hooks (e.g. terminal-notifier) are preserved untouched.</li>
                    <li>Idle "Claude is waiting for your input" reminders are filtered; only permission requests and real notifications flip state to needs-input.</li>
                </ul>
                <h2>Reliability</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Custom notification sounds now play via NSSound directly to avoid macOS UNNotificationSound falling back to the default tone.</li>
                    <li>Cost estimate no longer "flickers" — per-session token accumulation is preserved across transient file-read failures, and model/rate matching is deterministic.</li>
                    <li>Dashboard status and the system notification now flip at the exact same moment.</li>
                </ul>
                <h2>Preferences</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Polling interval setting removed — status transitions now arrive via hooks, so polling is background-only and fixed at 3 seconds.</li>
                </ul>
            ]]></description>
